What is the area of each congruent rectangle in the figure below?

\begin{center}
\includegraphics[scale=0.25]{images/area_color.png}
\end{center}
}

\textbf{Answer:} The area of the large square (outer perimeter) is $13^2$ or 169 sq. cm.  The area of the inner square is $5^2$ or 25 sq. cm.  Subtracting, we find the total area of the four congruent rectangles is $144$ sq. cm.  Each rectangle is $\displaystyle \frac{144}{4}=\boxed{36}$ sq. cm.
